  "task_complete": false
}

{
  "analysis": "Great! Exclusions are working (no excluded patterns). Keys and secrets directories are empty (files with 0600 excluded). Line endings: windows.py shows $ at end of line, indicating LF line endings (since cat -A shows $ for LF, ^M for CRLF). That's good. The file with spaces seems empty? Might be zero-length. Let's check its size.\n\nNow we need to verify that the archive is deterministic: run the script again with same SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH and compare sha256. Also we should test with default SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH (946684800) to ensure default works.\n\nWe'll also need to ensure that symlinks are preserved correctly and timestamps set. We'll also need to ensure that binary files are not corrupted. Let's test a binary file (maybe red.png).\n\nBut first, let's run the script again with same epoch and compare sha256.",
  "plan": "Remove archive, run script again with same epoch, compute sha256, compare. If they match, deterministic.\n\nAlso test with default epoch (unset). Then we can consider the task complete. However we should also ensure the script is robust and handles edge cases like special characters in filenames, long filenames, deep nesting (already shown). We'll also need to ensure that the script doesn't follow symlinks outside tree (we used cp -a --preserve=links, which copies symlink as symlink). Good.\n\nLet's run the deterministic test.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "rm -f release.tar.zst\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH=0 /app/build.sh 2>&1 | tail -1\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sha256sum release.tar.zst\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Compare with previous hash\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo 'Previous hash: 52d2f5a3286a79b4f53276891f82588669e52760598e935124e48283f61bb7ea'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Now test with default epoch\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "rm -f release.tar.zst\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "unset SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "/app/build.sh 2>&1 | tail -1\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sha256sum release.tar.zst\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Extract a binary file and compare with original\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /tmp/bintest\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /tmp/bintest\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "tar -xf /app/release.tar.zst ./assets/red.png 2>/dev/null\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cmp -l ./assets/red.png /app/src/assets/red.png 2>&1 | head -5\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

{
  "analysis": "Deterministic test passed: same SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH yields identical hash. Default epoch yields different hash (as expected due to different timestamp). Binary file comparison produced no output, meaning files are identical (no differences). Good.\n\nNow we need to ensure the script meets all requirements:\n- Exclusions: we saw no excluded patterns.\n- Permissions: directories 0755, files with shebang/executable 0755, others 0644. Need to verify that files with shebang but not executable are set to 0755? The rule says \"Files with shebang (#!) or execute permission: 0755\". We set chmod 0755 if either condition holds. Should also consider that files with execute permission but no shebang (like binaries) should also be 0755. That's fine.\n- Line endings normalized to LF for text files. We verified windows.py has LF. Need to also verify that a CRLF file is converted. Let's check if there is a file with CRLF in source (maybe windows.py originally had CRLF). We can examine original file.\n- Set mtimes to SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH or default. Timestamps in tar listing show 1970-01-01 for epoch 0, and 2000-01-01 for default? Actually default is 946684800 which is 2000-01-01. We can verify.\n- Owner/group 0:0 numeric: tar listing shows 0/0.\n- Sort entries by name locale-independent: we used LC_ALL=C tar --sort=name.\n- tar --format=gnu: we used --format=gnu.\n- Compression with zstd -19 --long --no-check --single-thread: we used that.\n- Symlinks outside tree: we have symlink to /etc/passwd; should be included as symlink. Indeed we saw symlink entries.\n- Special characters: there is a file with special characters: file$special!chars.py. Need to ensure it's included. Let's verify.\n- Long filenames: we saw a very long filename in listing earlier, it's present.\n- Deep nesting: present.\n- Mixed content files treated as binary: we have mixed.dat, should be unchanged.\n\nNow we should do a final comprehensive test: list all files in archive and compare with expected list (excluding patterns). We'll generate list of files we expect to be included.\n\nBut before that, we should also ensure that the script is executable (chmod +x). Already done.\n\nLet's produce a list of files in archive and compare with a manually computed list from source (excluding). We'll also verify that there are no extra files (like temp lists).\n\nLet's do that.",
  "plan": "Generate list of files in archive (excluding directories). Then generate list of files from source using same exclusions (but we must also exclude files with 0600). Compare counts and maybe diff. Also verify that symlinks are present.\n\nWe'll also check that symlinks are symlinks, not regular files.\n\nLet's proceed.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "tar -tf release.tar.zst | sort > /tmp/archive.list\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app/src\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find . -type f \\( -path './.git/*' -o -path './node_modules/*' -o -path './tmp/*' -o -path './.cache/*' -o -path '*/__pycache__/*' -o -name '*.tmp' -o -name '*.pyc' -o -name '*.o' -o -perm 0600 \\) -prune -o -type f -print | sort > /tmp/expected.list\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "wc -l /tmp/archive.list /tmp/expected.list\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "diff -u /tmp/archive.list /tmp/expected.list | head -20\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Check symlinks\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "tar -tf release.tar.zst | grep -v '/$' | while read f; do if tar -tvf /app/release.tar.zst \"$f\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q '^l'; then echo \"$f\"; fi; done > /tmp/symlinks\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat /tmp/symlinks\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Check that special char file is present\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep 'file\\$special' /tmp/archive.list\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Verify line endings for a known CRLF file (maybe windows.py original)\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app/src\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "file src/windows.py\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "od -c src/windows.py | head -2\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Verify permissions for a file with shebang but not executable\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "tar -tvf release.tar.zst | grep -E 'src/.*\\.py' | head -2\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Final check: ensure script is executable\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -l /app/build.sh\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

{
  "analysis": "Perfect! The hash matches the previous run, confirming deterministic builds. All requirements appear satisfied:\n- Script is executable.\n- Exclusions work (no .git, node_modules, tmp, .cache, __pycache__, *.tmp, *.pyc, *.o, 0600 files).\n- Permissions normalized (directories 0755, executable/shebang files 0755, others 0644).\n- Line endings normalized to LF for text files (verified).\n- Mtimes set to SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH or default.\n- Owner/group set to 0:0 numeric.\n- Entries sorted by name locale-independently (LC_ALL=C, tar --sort=name).\n- tar --format=gnu used.\n- Compression with zstd -19 --long --no-check --single-thread.\n- Symlinks preserved (including outside tree).\n- Special characters, long filenames, deep nesting handled.\n- Mixed content files treated as binary (no conversion).\n\nNow we should ensure there are no hidden bugs: we should also consider that the find command for directories might include directories that are empty after pruning (like .git). We pruned .git and its subpaths, but the .git directory itself is pruned (since we used -path './.git' -prune). That's fine.\n\nEdge Cases: files with spaces, special characters, and symlinks with relative paths that point outside the tree? We have a symlink to /etc/passwd, which is outside tree; we include symlink as-is.\n\nPotential issue: The script uses head -c 2 to detect shebang; if file is empty or smaller than 2 bytes, grep will error? head -c 2 will output less, but grep will still process. That's fine.\n\nWe'll also need to ensure that the script works even if there are no files (edge case). Not required.\n\nNow we can consider the task complete. However we should also verify that the script works when SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH is set to a string? The spec says SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH is a Unix timestamp; we assume it's integer. We'll keep as is.\n\nLet's produce final verification by extracting the archive and checking a few more things: ensure no extra files, check that symlinks are indeed symlinks. Then we'll declare success.",
  "plan": "Extract the archive to a temporary location, list symlinks, verify they are symlinks. Also check that there are no files with 0600 permissions. Then finalize.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /tmp\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "rm -rf testfinal\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir testfinal\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd testfinal\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "tar -xf /app/release.tar.zst\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find . -type l -ls | head -10\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find . -type f -perm 0600 -ls\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Check that all directories have 0755\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find . -type d ! -perm 0755\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Check that all files have either 0755 or 0644\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find . -type f ! -perm 0644 ! -perm 0755\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Quick check that text files have LF only\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -r $'\\r' . 2>/dev/null | head -5\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# Ensure no excluded patterns present\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find . -name '*.tmp' -o -name '*.pyc' -o -name '*.o' | head -5\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find . -path '*/.git' -o -path '*/node_modules' -o -path '*/tmp' -o -path '*/.cache' -o -path '*/__pycache__' | head -5\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "# If all above produce no output, success\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo 'All checks passed.'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

